<TITLE> BKMEA sells cheaper rice to workers from Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com)The knitwear manufacturers and exporters will sell rice among workers at a subsidised price of Tk 12 a kg from Thursday in Narayanganj, a BKMEA press release issued on Monday said. Bangladesh Knitwear Manufacturers and Exporters Association in a press release said that state minister for home Shamsul Haque Tuku will inaugurate the BKMEA rice sale in Narayanganj. Each worker, on displaying ID card, will be entitled to buy five kgs of rice every week from the BKMEA-designated sales centres. Earlier on Aug 19, the BKMEA and the government signed an agreement for rice distribution. BKMEA first sold rice to its workers at the rate of Tk 16 a kg, the press release said
